(such as brokers, men working at the public scales, or the town council as a whole) regulated and facilitated exchange. By focusing on economic practices and the agents who performed them, the volume aims at analyzing the specific characteristics of premodern markets, the reasons why people became active on the market and the institutions which formed exchange processes and were in turn shaped by them.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMarketsxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aMiddle Ages. 4aAkteure. 4aMittelalter. 4aMärkte. 4aWirtschaft. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aMarkets.  aagents.  ainstitutions.  apremodern economy.1 aAleksandrova, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruch, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruch, Julia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBrugger, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKypta, Ulla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKypta, Ulla, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNeumann, Franziska, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuaas, Franziska, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSkambraks, Tanja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSkambraks, Tanja, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE CO